cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.PL, cs.CC

This paper deals with reasoning about belief change in the context of actions and observations, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves formal logic and reasoning, which suggests cs.LO as another likely sub-category. The use of transition systems and operators for belief change also suggests cs.MA and cs.PL as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves some complexity analysis, which suggests cs.CC as a possible sub-category.
